jsx-no-leaked-render

Prevents falsy numeric values from leaking into JSX when using the && operator.

Source: https://github.com/oxc-project/tsgolint/pull/556

The Problem

  {count && <Badge>{count}</Badge>}

When count is 0, React renders the string "0" visibly in the DOM.
When count is NaN, React renders "NaN". Both are bugs.

What Gets Flagged

  Type      Flagged   Reason
  --------  -------   ------------------------------------------
  number    yes       Could be 0 or NaN, which render visibly
  bigint    yes       Could be 0n, which renders as "0"
  any       yes       Could be any of the above
  string    no        React 18+ treats "" as null (safe)
  boolean   no        false is ignored by React
  null      no        Ignored by React
  undefined no        Ignored by React
  object    no        Always truthy

Safe Alternatives

  {count > 0 && <Badge>{count}</Badge>}
  {!!count && <Badge>{count}</Badge>}
  {Boolean(count) && <Badge>{count}</Badge>}
  {count ? <Badge>{count}</Badge> : null}

Why Strings Are Not Flagged

React 18+ changed empty string behavior: "" is now coalesced to null in the
reconciler, creating no DOM text node. This was fixed in facebook/react#22807.
Before React 18, empty strings created empty text nodes. Now they're safe.

Non-zero number literals (1, 42, -1) are also not flagged since they're
always truthy.
